        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Vicki Morris was a reporter and editorialist for the Communist Party, USA newspaper the 
                <emph render="italic">Daily World</emph> (established 1968) and its successor, the 
                <emph render="italic">People's Daily World</emph>, and the daughter of George Morris (1903-), an author, labor journalist, and the chair of the Labor Commission of the Communist Party, USA.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>This collection contains clippings of Vicki Morris's articles and editorials as well as photos of Morris. PLEASE DIRECT FURTHER INQUIRIES TO: peter.filardo@nyu.edu</p>
